history.text: Have you seen La La Land?

La La Land is a 2016 American musical romantic comedy-drama film written and directed by
Damien Chazelle. It stars Ryan Gosling as a jazz pianist and Emma Stone as an aspiring actress,
who meet and fall in love in Los Angeles while pursuing their dreams. The film's title refers
simultaneously to music, the city of Los Angeles, and to the idiom for being out of touch with
reality.
